{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":36823,"duration_api_ms":36795,"num_turns":1,"result":"```json\n{\n  \"change_summary\": \"Thirteenth remediation round addressing 4 amendments (3 unique issues): (1) Added three new test functions covering jitter range validation, jitter cap enforcement, and clean teardown classification. jitter_enabled_backoff_stays_within_expected_range verifies attempt-1 backoff with jitter falls in [3.75s, 6.25s) across 20 samples. jitter_never_exceeds_backoff_cap verifies no jittered backoff exceeds 60s for attempts 1–10. clean_timeout_teardown_yields_timeout_without_warning spawns a killable process, triggers timeout, and asserts FailureClass::Timeout with no 'teardown not confirmed' warning. (2+4) Fixed binary.exists() misclassification for bare-name binaries: replaced !binary.exists() with !binary.is_absolute() || !binary.exists(). For bare names returned by resolve_binary (OS PATH lookup), ENOENT always maps to BinaryNotFound since PATH resolution failed. For absolute paths (from explicit search_paths), the exists() check still guards against misclassifying missing-interpreter ENOENT as BinaryNotFound. (3) Fixed jitter exceeding backoff_cap: added .min(self.backoff_cap) after apply_jitter() so the jitter multiplier (up to 1.25×) cannot push the result above the configured cap.\",\n  \"outstanding_risks\": [\n    \"Process group kill cannot be implemented due to #![forbid(unsafe_code)] — pre_exec(setsid) requires unsafe, and std::process::Command::process_group is nightly-only. Grandchildren spawned by claude/codex CLI may survive as orphans after the parent is killed on timeout/cancel.\",\n    \"The confirm_teardown 'resisting-kill returning false' scenario (amendment 1a/1b) cannot be tested end-to-end because SIGKILL is uncatchable on Linux — no userspace process can resist it. The only scenario where confirm_teardown returns false is kernel-level uninterruptible sleep (D state), which cannot be reliably reproduced in a test. The clean teardown path (killed process → true → Timeout) is tested by both spawn_and_wait_timeout_returns_timeout_failure and clean_timeout_teardown_yields_timeout_without_warning.\",\n    \"The BinaryNotFound failure class name is used for both missing binaries and missing API keys. Doc comments clarify this dual use as a general 'fatal infrastructure prerequisite' signal, but operator logs will still show 'binary_not_found' for missing env vars.\",\n    \"The jitter implementation uses SystemTime subsec_nanos which is not cryptographically random, but provides sufficient dispersion for retry staggering. Two processes calling within the same nanosecond would get identical jitter, but this is vanishingly unlikely in practice.\"\n  ],\n  \"steps\": [\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Fixed jitter exceeding backoff_cap in retry_policy.rs: added .min(self.backoff_cap) after Self::apply_jitter(capped) in backoff_for_attempt(). Previously, attempt 5 was capped to 60s then multiplied by up to 1.25, producing ~75s. Now the post-jitter value is re-capped to 60s.\",\n      \"order\": 1,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Fixed binary.exists() misclassification for bare-name binaries in process_backend.rs:999-1005: changed condition from `error.kind() == NotFound && !binary.exists()` to `error.kind() == NotFound && (!binary.is_absolute() || !binary.exists())`. For bare names (PATH lookup), ENOENT always means BinaryNotFound. For absolute paths, exists() still distinguishes missing-binary from missing-interpreter. Updated comment to explain the bare-name vs absolute-path distinction.\",\n      \"order\": 2,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Added jitter_enabled_backoff_stays_within_expected_range test in retry_policy_test.rs: runs 20 samples of backoff_for_attempt(1) on default policy (jitter enabled) and asserts each falls within [3.75s, 6.25s), validating the ±25% jitter range.\",\n      \"order\": 3,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Added jitter_never_exceeds_backoff_cap test in retry_policy_test.rs: runs 20 samples per attempt for attempts 1–10 and asserts no jittered backoff exceeds 60s (backoff_cap), directly validating the re-cap-after-jitter fix from step 1.\",\n      \"order\": 4,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Added clean_timeout_teardown_yields_timeout_without_warning test in process_backend_test.rs: spawns a sleeping process with a 2s timeout, asserts the error is InvocationFailed with FailureClass::Timeout, and asserts the details do not contain 'teardown not confirmed', verifying the clean confirm_teardown → Timeout path end-to-end.\",\n      \"order\": 5,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Unclean teardown test (confirm_teardown returning false → TransportFailure): skipped because SIGKILL cannot be caught or ignored on Linux, making it impossible to create a userspace process that resists kill within the 2s grace period. The only trigger is kernel uninterruptible sleep (D state) which cannot be reliably reproduced in CI.\",\n      \"order\": 6,\n      \"status\": \"skipped\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"description\": \"Verified all 683 tests pass, cargo clippy -- -D warnings clean, cargo fmt --check clean.\",\n      \"order\": 7,\n      \"status\": \"completed\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"validation_evidence\": [\n    \"cargo test: 683 passed, 0 failed, 0 ignored across all test binaries\",\n    \"cargo clippy -- -D warnings: no warnings or errors\",\n    \"cargo fmt --check: no formatting differences (exit 0)\",\n    \"jitter_enabled_backoff_stays_within_expected_range: 20 samples of backoff_for_attempt(1) all fall within [3.75s, 6.25s), validating ±25% jitter on the 5s base delay\",\n    \"jitter_never_exceeds_backoff_cap: 200 samples (20 per attempt × 10 attempts) all ≤ 60s, confirming the re-cap-after-jitter fix prevents overflow above backoff_cap\",\n    \"clean_timeout_teardown_yields_timeout_without_warning: spawned process killed by timeout, confirm_teardown returns true, error classified as Timeout with no 'teardown not confirmed' in details\",\n    \"spawn_and_wait_timeout_returns_timeout_failure: pre-existing test still passes — confirms artifact preservation (.failed.raw) and Timeout classification for the happy-path timeout\",\n    \"spawn_missing_binary_returns_binary_not_found: still passes — bare name 'claude' with empty PATH returns BinaryNotFound via the !binary.is_absolute() branch (bare names always classify ENOENT as BinaryNotFound)\",\n    \"All 72 workflow_engine_test tests pass with --features test-stub: retry exhaustion, resume-from-failed, cancellation during backoff, and preflight failure tests unaffected by jitter cap fix\",\n    \"All 7 tmux_adapter_test tests pass: timeout cleanup, cancel with SIGTERM/SIGKILL, output matching — tmux paths unaffected by process_backend spawn classification change\"\n  ]\n}\n```","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"2ab56341-dc03-426c-ace5-dda05f3b0827","total_cost_usd":0.5053240000000001,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":72386,"cache_read_input_tokens":11303,"output_tokens":1890,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":72386,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":2,"outputTokens":1890,"cacheReadInputTokens":11303,"cacheCreationInputTokens":72386,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.5053240000000001,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"837ea910-2e3b-45cf-93b9-87fbabac741e"}
